International Brief -- Daewoo Corp.:
   Unit Wins $957 Million Job
   For Highway in Pakistan
The project, which includes the construction of 74 bridges
of various lengths, will be undertaken on a turnkey basis
with Daewoo handling design, detail engineering, procurement
and construction. The design fee is $9 million, the company
said.
   Chang Young Soo, president of Daewoo's construction
division, said the contract is the largest international road
contract ever awarded by Pakistan. Construction is scheduled
to be completed by April 1995.